EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Padavan, S. 8705, and by the Committee on Rules (at the request of Assembly Member Silver), A. 11755, “AN ACT to amend the real property tax law, in relation to tax abatement and tax exemption for industrial and commercial work on properties in a city of one million or more persons”.
EventItemMatterName: Tax abatement/ exemption on commercial work (S.8705/A.11755)

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this SLR be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Smith, S. 8289-A, and Assembly Member Pheffer, A. 11222-A, “AN ACT in relation to authorizing the city of New York to sell waterfront property and land under water appurtenant thereto, owned by such city, consisting of a tax lot improved with a pier in the county of Queens, known as Beach 84th Street Pier”.
